-- Second London Man in a Week Arrested on Terror Charges
-- B y   J e r e m y   H o d g e s
-- 2012-04-04T16:14:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/second-london-man-in-a-week-arrested-on-terror-charges.html
London  police charged a 24-year-old
man over a terror plot today, making him the second in a week to
face such allegations.  The east London man was scheduled to appear in Westminster
Magistrates Court today to be charged with “the intention of
assisting another to commit acts of terrorism.”  Another man, also 24, appeared earlier today charged with
offenses under British terror laws, Metropolitan Police said in
an e-mailed statement.  “The arrests were a part of a pre-planned, intelligence-
led operation into alleged fundraising for terrorism overseas,”
according to the police statement. Searches were conducted at
four homes in east London.  On April 2, along with the two men that appeared in court
today officers from the MPS counterterrorism unit arrested a 21-
year-old woman who has since been released without charge and a
30-year-old man who still being held.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeremy Hodges in London at 
